speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for War (1) whether he will make inquiries with a view to putting an end to the system under which drivers of coaches, hired by his Department in


Burnley, receive £7 per week in addition to maintenance, and by which they have had to sleep in the coaches for six weeks past though the coaches have for the most part been standing idle;

(2) whether he is aware that six coaches have been hired by his Department at Burnley, Lancashire, for work at a camp in Yorkshire at a cost of 30s. per day plus drivers' wages at £1 per day, in addition to maintenance while standing, and at a cost of £5 2s. 6d. per day in addition to drivers' keep while running; and will he consider devising a less costly and wasteful method?
